description: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime,it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.

name: Torterra
description: Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground,a gigantic Torterra dwelled.

name: Chimchar
description: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly.Even rain cant extinguish the fire.

name: Monferno
description: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on itstail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.

name: Infernape
description: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature.It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.

name: Piplup
description: It doesnt like to be taken care of. Its difficult tobond with since it wont listen to its Trainer.

name: Prinplup
description: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, everyone of them believes it is the most important.

name: Empoleon
description: It swims as fast as a jet boat. The edges of itswings are sharp and can slice apart drifting ice.

name: Starly
description: They flock in great numbers. Though small, theyflap their wings with great power.

name: Staravia
description: They maintain huge flocks, although fierce scufflesbreak out between various flocks.

name: Staraptor
description: The muscles in its wings and legs are strong.It can easily fly while gripping a small Pokémon.

name: Bidoof
description: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It ismore agile and active than it appears.

name: Bibarel
description: It busily makes its nest with stacks of branches androots it has cut up with its sharp incisors.

name: Kricketot
description: It chats with others using the sounds of its collidingantennae. These sounds are fall hallmarks.

name: Kricketune
description: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chestwhen it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.

name: Shinx
description: The extension and contraction of its musclesgenerates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

name: Luxio
description: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperageto cause fainting. They live in small groups.

name: Luxray
description: When its eyes gleam gold, it can spot hidingprey—even those taking shelter behind a wall.

name: Budew
description: When it feels the suns warm touch, it opens its budto release pollen. It lives alongside clear pools.

name: Roserade
description: Luring prey with a sweet scent, it uses poison whipson its arms to poison, bind, and finish off the prey.

name: Cranidos
description: It was resurrected from an iron ball-like fossil.It downs prey with its headbutts.

name: Rampardos
description: Its skull withstands impacts of any magnitude. As aresult, its brain never gets the chance to grow.

name: Shieldon
description: It habitually polishes its face by rubbing it againsttree trunks. It is weak to attacks from behind.

name: Bastiodon
description: When they lined up side by side, no foe couldbreak through. They shielded their young inthat way.

name: Burmy
description: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it coversitself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

name: Wormadam
description: Its appearance changes depending on where itevolved. The materials on hand become a part ofits body.

name: Mothim
description: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honeycollected by Combee.

name: Combee
description: The trio is together from birth. It constantly gathershoney from flowers to please Vespiquen.

name: Vespiquen
description: It houses its colony in cells in its body and releasesvarious pheromones to make those grubs do its bidding.

name: Pachirisu
description: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity.It stores them with berries in tree holes.

name: Buizel
description: It swims by rotating its two tails like a screw.When it dives, its flotation sac collapses.

name: Floatzel
description: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac.It assists in the rescues of drowning people.

name: Cherubi
description: Sunlight colors it red. When the small ball isdrained of nutrients, it shrivels to herald evolution.

name: Cherrim
description: During times of strong sunlight, its bud blooms,its petals open fully, and it becomes very active.

name: Shellos
description: Beware of pushing strongly on its squishy body,as it makes a mysterious purple fluid ooze out.

name: Gastrodon
description: When its natural enemy attacks, it oozes purplefluid and escapes.

name: Ambipom
description: They work in large colonies and make rings bylinking their tails, apparently in friendship.

name: Drifloon
description: A Pokémon formed by the spirits of people and Pokémon.It loves damp, humid seasons.

name: Drifblim
description: It carries people and Pokémon when it flies.But since it only drifts, it can end up anywhere.

name: Buneary
description: Its ears are always rolled up. They can be forcefullyextended to shatter even a large boulder.

name: Lopunny
description: Extremely cautious, it quickly bounds off when itsenses danger.

name: Mismagius
description: It chants incantations. While they usually tormenttargets, some chants bring happiness.

name: Honchkrow
description: If one utters a deep cry, many Murkrow gatherquickly. For this, it is called “Summoner of Night.”

name: Glameow
description: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate.Its fickleness is very popular among some.

name: Purugly
description: It would claim another Pokémons nest as its ownif it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.

name: Chingling
description: Each time it hops, it makes a ringing sound.It deafens foes by emitting high-frequency cries.

name: Stunky
description: It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stenchspreads over a mile radius, driving Pokémon away.

name: Skuntank
description: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tailto attack. Its range is over 160 feet.

name: Bronzor
description: Ancient people believed that the pattern onBronzors back contained a mysterious power.

name: Bronzong
description: In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as abringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.

name: Bonsly
description: It prefers arid environments. It leaks water from itseyes to adjust its bodys fluid levels.

name: Mime Jr.
description: In an attempt to confuse its enemy, it mimics theenemys movements. Then it wastes no time inmaking itself scarce!

name: Happiny
description: It carries a round, egg-shaped rock in its bellypouch and gives the rock to its friends.

name: Chatot
description: It mimics the cries of other Pokémon to trick theminto thinking its one of them. This way they wontattack it.

name: Spiritomb
description: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It isbound to a fissure in an odd keystone.

name: Gible
description: It nests in horizontal holes warmed by geothermalheat. Foes who get too close can expect to bepounced on and bitten.

name: Gabite
description: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in cavesand hoards the loot in its nest.

name: Garchomp
description: When it folds up its body and extends its wings,it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.

name: Munchlax
description: It hides food under its long body hair. However,it forgets it has hidden the food.

name: Riolu
description: It uses the shapes of auras, which changeaccording to emotion, to communicate with others.

name: Lucario
description: By catching the aura emanating from others, it canread their thoughts and movements.

name: Hippopotas
description: It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration,it expels grainy sand from its body.

name: Hippowdon
description: It brandishes its gaping mouth in a display offearsome strength. It raises vast quantities of sandwhile attacking.

name: Skorupi
description: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison.It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.

name: Drapion
description: It takes pride in its strength. Even though it cantear foes apart, it finishes them off withpowerful poison.

name: Croagunk
description: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foesoff guard to jab them with toxic fingers.

name: Toxicroak
description: It has a poison sac at its throat. When it croaks,the stored poison is churned for greater potency.

name: Carnivine
description: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, thenchomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

name: Finneon
description: The line running down its side can store sunlight.It shines vividly at night.

name: Lumineon
description: It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey byflashing the patterns on its four tail fins.

name: Mantyke
description: The pattern on its back varies by region.It often swims in a school of Remoraid.

name: Snover
description: During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountainslower reaches. It returns to the snow-coveredsummit in the spring.

name: Abomasnow
description: It blankets wide areas in snow by whipping upblizzards. It is also known as “The Ice Monster.”

name: Weavile
description: It lives in snowy regions. It carves patterns in treeswith its claws as a signal to others.

name: Magnezone
description: Sometimes the magnetism emitted by Magnezone istoo strong, making them attract each other so theycannot move.

name: Lickilicky
description: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Gettingtoo close to it will leave you soaked with drool.

name: Rhyperior
description: From holes in its palms, it fires out Geodude.Its carapace can withstand volcanic eruptions.

name: Tangrowth
description: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines.Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.

name: Electivire
description: As its electric charge amplifies, blue sparks beginto crackle between its horns.

name: Magmortar
description: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheitfrom the ends of its arms. It lives involcanic craters.

name: Togekiss
description: As everyone knows, it visits peaceful regions,bringing them gifts of kindness andsweet blessings.

name: Yanmega
description: It prefers to battle by biting apart foes headsinstantly while flying by at high speed.

name: Leafeon
description: When you see Leafeon asleep in a patch ofsunshine, youll know it is using photosynthesisto produce clean air.

name: Glaceon
description: By controlling its body heat, it can freeze theatmosphere around it to make adiamond-dust flurry.

name: Gliscor
description: It observes prey while hanging inverted frombranches. When the chance presents itself,it swoops!

name: Mamoswine
description: A frozen Mamoswine was dug from ice dating back10,000 years. This Pokémon has been around along, long, long time.

name: Porygon-Z
description: Additional software was installed to make it a betterPokémon. It began acting oddly, however.

name: Gallade
description: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking,its attacks burst out first, fast, and fierce.

name: Probopass
description: It exudes strong magnetism from all over.It controls three small units called Mini-Noses.

name: Dusknoir
description: It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body andguide them home.

name: Froslass
description: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly-60 degrees Fahrenheit. What seems to be its bodyis actually hollow.

name: Rotom
description: Research continues on this Pokémon, which couldbe the power source of a unique motor.

name: Uxie
description: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said thatit can wipe out the memory of those who seeits eyes.

name: Mesprit
description: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taughthumans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

name: Azelf
description: Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at thebottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

name: Dialga
description: A Pokémon spoken of in legend. It is said that timebegan moving when Dialga was born.

name: Palkia
description: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimensionparallel to ours. It appears in mythology.

name: Heatran
description: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with itscross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: Regigigas
description: It is said to have made Pokémon that look likeitself from a special ice mountain, rocks,and magma.

name: Giratina
description: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on thereverse side of ours, where common knowledge isdistorted and strange.

name: Cresselia
description: Shiny particles are released from its wings like aveil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: Phione
description: When the water warms, they inflate the flotation sacon their heads and drift languidly on the seain packs.

name: Manaphy
description: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bondwith any kind of Pokémon.

name: Darkrai
description: It chases people and Pokémon from its territory bycausing them to experience deep,nightmarish slumbers.

name: Shaymin
description: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantlytransform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

name: Arceus
description: According to the legends of Sinnoh, this Pokémonemerged from an egg and shaped all there is inthis world.

name: Victini
description: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainerswith Victini always win, regardless of the typeof encounter.

name: Snivy
description: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movementsswifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.

name: Servine
description: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swiftmovements befuddle its foes, and it then attackswith a vine whip.

name: Serperior
description: It only gives its all against strong opponents whoare not fazed by the glare from Serperiorsnoble eyes.

name: Tepig
description: It can deftly dodge its foes attacks while shootingfireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before iteats them.

name: Pignite
description: The more it eats, the more fuel it has to make thefire in its stomach stronger. This fills it with evenmore power.

name: Emboar
description: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on firewith its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

name: Oshawott
description: The scalchop on its stomach isnt just used forbattle—it can be used to break open hard berriesas well.

name: Dewott
description: Strict training is how it learns its flowingdouble-scalchop technique.

name: Samurott
description: In the time it takes a foe to blink, it can draw andsheathe the seamitars attached to its front legs.

name: Patrat
description: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keepwatch for days. They use their tails to communicatewith others.

name: Watchog
description: Using luminescent matter, it makes its eyes andbody glow and stuns attacking opponents.

name: Lillipup
description: The long hair around its face provides an amazingradar that lets it sense subtle changes inits surroundings.

name: Herdier
description: This very loyal Pokémon helps Trainers, and it alsotakes care of other Pokémon.

name: Stoutland
description: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in themountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

name: Purrloin
description: Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down theirguard, they find their items taken. It attacks withsharp claws.

name: Liepard
description: Their beautiful form comes from the muscles theyhave developed. They run silently in the night.

name: Pansage
description: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-lookingPokémon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.

name: Simisage
description: It attacks enemies with strikes of its thorn-coveredtail. This Pokémon is wild tempered.

name: Pansear
description: Very intelligent, it roasts berries before eating them.It likes to help people.

name: Simisear
description: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embersfrom its head and tail to sear its opponents.

name: Panpour
description: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is fullof nutrients. It waters plants with it using its tail.

name: Simipour
description: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is sopowerful, it can destroy a concrete wall.

name: Munna
description: This Pokémon appears before people and Pokémonwho are having nightmares and eats those dreams.

name: Musharna
description: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packedwith the dreams of people and Pokémon.

name: Pidove
description: This very forgetful Pokémon will wait for a neworder from its Trainer even though it alreadyhas one.

name: Tranquill
description: Many people believe that, deep in the forest whereTranquill live, there is a peaceful place where thereis no war.

name: Unfezant
description: Males swing their head plumage to threatenopponents. The females flying abilities surpassthose of the males.

name: Blitzle
description: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear.It can catch lightning with its mane and storethe electricity.

name: Zebstrika
description: When this ill-tempered Pokémon runs wild, itshoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

name: Roggenrola
description: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressedunderground, its body is as hard as steel.

name: Boldore
description: Because its energy was too great to be contained,the energy leaked and formed orange crystals.

name: Gigalith
description: The solar rays it absorbs are processed in itsenergy core and fired as a ball of light.

name: Woobat
description: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emitsultrasonic waves from its nose to learn aboutits surroundings.

name: Swoobat
description: It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonicwaves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.

name: Drilbur
description: It makes its way swiftly through the soil by puttingboth claws together and rotating at high speed.

name: Excadrill
description: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill hasevolved into steel strong enough to bore throughiron plates.

name: Audino
description: Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell howsomeone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.

name: Timburr
description: These Pokémon appear at building sites and helpout with construction. They always carrysquared logs.

name: Gurdurr
description: With strengthened bodies, they skillfully wield steelbeams to take down buildings.

name: Conkeldurr
description: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how tomake concrete more than 2,000 years ago.

name: Tympole
description: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound wavesimperceptible to humans and warns othersof danger.

name: Palpitoad
description: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, theycan make waves in water or earthquake-likevibrations on land.

name: Seismitoad
description: It increases the power of its punches by vibratingthe bumps on its fists. It can turn a boulder torubble with one punch.

name: Throh
description: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. WildThroh use vines to weave their own belts.

name: Sawk
description: Desiring the strongest karate chop, they secludethemselves in mountains and train without sleeping.

name: Sewaddle
description: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews upleaves and sews them with sticky thread extrudedfrom its mouth.

name: Swadloon
description: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliagebecause the nutrients they make from fallen leavesnourish the plant life.

name: Leavanny
description: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothingfor it from leaves by using the sticky silk secretedfrom its mouth.

name: Venipede
description: It discovers what is going on around it by using thefeelers on its head and tail. It is brutally aggressive.

name: Whirlipede
description: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like awheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.

name: Scolipede
description: It clasps its prey with the claws on its neck until itstops moving. Then it finishes it off withdeadly poison.

name: Cottonee
description: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton fromits body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distractthe attacker.

name: Whimsicott
description: They appear along with whirlwinds. They pullpranks, such as moving furniture and leaving ballsof cotton in homes.

name: Petilil
description: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating oneof these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.

name: Lilligant
description: The fragrance of the garland on its head has arelaxing effect. It withers if a Trainer does not takegood care of it.

name: Basculin
description: Red- and blue-striped Basculin are very violent andalways fighting. They are also remarkably tasty.

name: Sandile
description: It moves along below the sands surface, exceptfor its nose and eyes. A dark membrane shields itseyes from the sun.

name: Krokorok
description: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protectivemembranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.

name: Krookodile
description: Very violent Pokémon, they try to clamp down onanything that moves in front of their eyes.

name: Darumaka
description: Darumakas droppings are hot, so people used toput them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.

name: Darmanitan
description: When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardensinto a stone-like form. Then it meditates andsharpens its mind.

name: Maractus
description: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive awaythe bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.

name: Dwebble
description: It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rockbreaks, the Pokémon remains agitated until itlocates a replacement.

name: Crustle
description: It possesses legs of enormous strength, enabling itto carry heavy slabs for many days, even whencrossing arid land.

name: Scraggy
description: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reducedamage by defensively pulling its skin up toits neck.

name: Scrafty
description: It pulls up its shed skin to protect itself whileit kicks. The bigger the crest, the more respectedit is.

name: Sigilyph
description: The guardians of an ancient city, they use theirpsychic power to attack enemies that invadetheir territory.

name: Yamask
description: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of peopleinterred in graves. Each retains memories of itsformer life.

name: Cofagrigus
description: It has been said that they swallow those who gettoo close and turn them into mummies. They like toeat gold nuggets.

name: Tirtouga
description: About 100 million years ago, these Pokémon swamin oceans. It is thought they also went on land toattack prey.

name: Carracosta
description: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slapfrom one of them is enough to open a hole in thebottom of a tanker.

name: Archen
description: Revived from a fossil, this Pokémon is thought tobe the ancestor of all bird Pokémon.

name: Archeops
description: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catchprey. From the ground, they use a running start totake flight.

name: Trubbish
description: The combination of garbage bags and industrialwaste caused the chemical reaction that createdthis Pokémon.

name: Garbodor
description: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishesthem off with foul-smelling poison gas belched fromits mouth.

name: Zorua
description: It changes so it looks just like its foe, tricks it, andthen uses that opportunity to flee.

name: Zoroark
description: Each has the ability to fool a large group of peoplesimultaneously. They protect their lair withillusory scenery.

name: Minccino
description: Minccino greet each other by grooming one anotherthoroughly with their tails.

name: Cinccino
description: Their white fur feels amazing to touch. Their furrepels dust and prevents static electricity frombuilding up.

name: Gothita
description: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychicpower. They are always staring at something.

name: Gothorita
description: Starlight is the source of their power. At night,they mark star positions by using psychic powerto float stones.

name: Gothitelle
description: Starry skies thousands of light-years away arevisible in the space distorted by their intensepsychic power.

name: Solosis
description: Because their bodies are enveloped in a specialliquid, they are fine in any environment, no matterhow severe.

name: Duosion
description: Since they have two divided brains, at times theysuddenly try to take two different actions at once.

name: Reuniclus
description: They use psychic power to control their arms,which are made of a special liquid. They can crushboulders psychically.

name: Ducklett
description: When attacked, it uses its feathers to splash water,escaping under cover of the spray.

name: Swanna
description: Despite their elegant appearance, they can flaptheir wings strongly and fly for thousands of miles.

name: Vanillite
description: The temperature of their breath is -58 degreesFahrenheit. They create snow crystals and makesnow fall in the areas around them.

name: Vanillish
description: They cool down the surrounding air and create iceparticles, which they use to freeze their foes.

name: Vanilluxe
description: If both heads get angry simultaneously, thisPokémon expels a blizzard, burying everythingin snow.

name: Deerling
description: Their coloring changes according to the seasonsand can be slightly affected by the temperature andhumidity as well.

name: Sawsbuck
description: They migrate according to the seasons. People cantell the season by looking at Sawsbucks horns.

name: Emolga
description: They live on treetops and glide using the inside ofa cape-like membrane while discharging electricity.

name: Karrablast
description: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when theyreceive electrical stimulation while they are in thesame place as Shelmet.

name: Escavalier
description: Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet,they defend themselves and attack with two lances.

name: Foongus
description: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, thenreleases poison spores. Why it resembles aPoké Ball is unknown.

name: Amoonguss
description: They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey,but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.

name: Frillish
description: They paralyze prey with poison, then drag themdown to their lairs, five miles below the surface.

name: Jellicent
description: Its body is mostly seawater. Its said theres acastle of ships Jellicent have sunk on the seafloor.

name: Alomomola
description: Floating in the open sea is how they live.When they find a wounded Pokémon,they embrace it and bring it to shore.

name: Joltik
description: Since it cant generate its own electricity, it sticksonto large-bodied Pokémon and absorbsstatic electricity.

name: Galvantula
description: They employ an electrically charged web to traptheir prey. While it is immobilized by shock,they leisurely consume it.

name: Ferroseed
description: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrageof spikes, which gives it a chance to escape byrolling away.

name: Ferrothorn
description: By swinging around its three spiky feelers andshooting spikes, it can obliterate an opponent.

name: Klink
description: Interlocking two bodies and spinning aroundgenerates the energy they need to live.

name: Klang
description: By changing the direction in which it rotates,it communicates its feelings to others. When angry,it rotates faster.

name: Klinklang
description: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speedfor a rapid energy charge.

name: Tynamo
description: While one alone doesnt have much power, a chainof many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

name: Eelektrik
description: It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it withelectricity from the round spots on its sides.Then it chomps.

name: Eelektross
description: With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey.Then they use their fangs to shock the preywith electricity.

name: Elgyem
description: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze itsopponents brain, causing unendurable headaches.

name: Beheeyem
description: Apparently, it communicates by flashing its threefingers, but those patterns havent been decoded.

name: Litwick
description: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide,it leeches off the life force of any who follow it.

name: Lampent
description: The spirits it absorbs fuel its baleful fire. It hangsaround hospitals waiting for people to pass on.

name: Chandelure
description: Being consumed in Chandelures flame burns upthe spirit, leaving the body behind.

name: Axew
description: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat.Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strongand sharp.

name: Fraxure
description: Their tusks can shatter rocks. Territory battlesbetween Fraxure can be intensely violent.

name: Haxorus
description: They are kind but can be relentless when defendingterritory. They challenge foes with tusks that cancut steel.

name: Cubchoo
description: Its nose is always running. It sniffs the snot back upbecause the mucus provides the raw material forits moves.

name: Beartic
description: They love the cold seas of the north. They createpathways across the ocean waters by freezing theirown breath.

name: Cryogonal
description: They are born in snow clouds. They use chainsmade of ice crystals to capture prey.

name: Shelmet
description: When it and Karrablast are together, and bothreceive electrical stimulation, they both evolve.

name: Accelgor
description: Having removed its heavy shell, it becomes verylight and can fight with ninja-like movements.

name: Stunfisk
description: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if steppedon by sumo wrestlers. It smiles whentransmitting electricity.

name: Mienfoo
description: It takes pride in the speed at which it can usemoves. What it loses in power, it makes up forin quantity.

name: Mienshao
description: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its armattacks come with such rapidity that they cannoteven be seen.

name: Druddigon
description: It races through narrow caves, using its sharp clawsto catch prey. The skin on its face is harder thana rock.

name: Golett
description: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move,but no one has yet been able to identifythis energy.

name: Golurk
description: It is said that Golurk were ordered to protectpeople and Pokémon by the ancient people whomade them.

name: Pawniard
description: Blades comprise this Pokémons entire body.If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them onstones by the river.

name: Bisharp
description: This pitiless Pokémon commands a group ofPawniard to hound prey into immobility. It thenmoves in to finish the prey off.

name: Bouffalant
description: They charge wildly and headbutt everything.Their headbutts have enough destructive force toderail a train.

name: Rufflet
description: They crush berries with their talons. They bravelystand up to any opponent, no matter how strongit is.

name: Braviary
description: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of thesky will not stop battling, even if injured.

name: Vullaby
description: Its wings are too tiny to allow it to fly. As the timeapproaches for it to evolve, it discards the bonesit was wearing.

name: Mandibuzz
description: They fly in circles around the sky. When they spotprey, they attack and carry it back to their nestwith ease.

name: Heatmor
description: Using their very hot, flame-covered tongues,they burn through Durants steel bodies andconsume their insides.

name: Durant
description: Individuals each play different roles in drivingHeatmor, their natural predator, away fromtheir colony.

name: Deino
description: They cannot see, so they tackle and bite to learnabout their surroundings. Their bodies are coveredin wounds.

name: Zweilous
description: The two heads do not get along. Whichever headeats more than the other gets to be the leader.

name: Hydreigon
description: The heads on their arms do not have brains.They use all three heads to consume anddestroy everything.

name: Larvesta
description: Said to have been born from the sun, it spews firefrom its horns and encases itself in a cocoon of firewhen it evolves.

name: Volcarona
description: A sea of fire engulfs the surroundings of theirbattles, since they use their six wings to scattertheir ember scales.

name: Cobalion
description: It has a body and heart of steel. Its glare issufficient to make even an unruly Pokémon obey it.

name: Terrakion
description: Its charge is strong enough to break through agiant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon isspoken of in legends.

name: Virizion
description: Its head sprouts horns as sharp as blades. Usingwhirlwind-like movements, it confounds and swiftlycuts opponents.

name: Tornadus
description: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud ofenergy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

name: Thundurus
description: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts oflightning. It flies around the Unova region firing offlightning bolts.

name: Reshiram
description: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world withfire. It helps those who want to build a worldof truth.

name: Zekrom
description: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world withlightning. It assists those who want to build anideal world.

name: Landorus
description: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountifulcrops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian ofthe Fields.”

name: Kyurem
description: This legendary ice Pokémon waits for a hero to fillin the missing parts of its body with truth or ideals.

name: Keldeo
description: It crosses the world, running over the surfaces ofoceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.

name: Meloetta
description: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power tomake Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.

name: Genesect
description: This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by TeamPlasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.

name: Chespin
description: The quills on its head are usually soft.When it flexes them, the points becomeso hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

name: Quilladin
description: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predatorsattacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.

name: Chesnaught
description: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank.It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

name: Fennekin
description: Eating a twig fills it with energy,and its roomy ears give vent to airhotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Braixen
description: It has a twig stuck in its tail. Withfriction from its tail fur, it sets thetwig on fire and launches into battle.

name: Delphox
description: It gazes into the flame at the tip ofits branch to achieve a focused state,which allows it to see into the future.

name: Froakie
description: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back.The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwisetake when attacked.

name: Frogadier
description: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precisecontrol, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

name: Greninja
description: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water.When it spins them and throws them at high speed,these stars can split metal in two.

name: Bunnelby
description: They use their large ears to dig burrows.They will dig the whole night through.

name: Diggersby
description: With their powerful ears, they can heftboulders of a ton or more with ease.They can be a big help at construction sites.

name: Fletchling
description: These friendly Pokémon send signalsto one another with beautiful chirpsand tail-feather movements.

name: Fletchinder
description: From its beak, it expels embers that setthe tall grass on fire. Then it pounces onthe bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.

name: Talonflame
description: In the fever of an exciting battle, itshowers embers from the gaps betweenits feathers and takes to the air.

name: Scatterbug
description: When under attack from bird Pokémon,it spews a poisonous black powderthat causes paralysis on contact.

name: Spewpa
description: It lives hidden within thicket shadows.When predators attack, it quickly bristles the furcovering its body in an effort to threaten them.

name: Vivillon
description: Vivillon with many different patterns arefound all over the world. These patternsare affected by the climate of their habitat.

name: Litleo
description: The stronger the opponent it faces,the more heat surges from its maneand the more power flows through its body.

name: Pyroar
description: The male with the largest mane of fireis the leader of the pride.

name: Flabébé
description: It draws out and controls the hidden powerof flowers. The flower Flabébé holdsis most likely part of its body.

name: Floette
description: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares forflowers that are starting to wilt. It drawsout the hidden power of flowers to battle.

name: Florges
description: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory,and it obtains power from basking in the energyemitted by flowering plants.

name: Skiddo
description: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live inharmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

name: Gogoat
description: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling bysubtle shifts in the grip on its horns.This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.

name: Pancham
description: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies,but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating.Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.

name: Pangoro
description: Although it possesses a violent temperament,it wont put up with bullying. It uses the leaf inits mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.

name: Furfrou
description: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makesit more elegant but also increases theswiftness of its movements.

name: Espurr
description: The organ that emits its intense psychic power issheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.

name: Meowstic
description: When in danger, it raises its ears andreleases enough psychic power togrind a 10-ton truck into dust.

name: Honedge
description: Apparently this Pokémon is born when adeparted spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itselfto people and drinks their life force.

name: Doublade
description: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords,which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacksand slash their enemies to ribbons.

name: Aegislash
description: Generations of kings were attended by thesePokémon, which used their spectral power tomanipulate and control people and Pokémon.

name: Spritzee
description: It emits a scent that enraptures thosewho smell it. This fragrance changesdepending on what it has eaten.

name: Aromatisse
description: It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant,and emits scents that its enemies dislike in orderto gain an edge in battle.

name: Swirlix
description: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudeswhite threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.

name: Slurpuff
description: It can distinguish the faintest of scents.It puts its sensitive sense of smell to useby helping pastry chefs in their work.

name: Inkay
description: Opponents who stare at the flashing of thelight-emitting spots on its body becomedazed and lose their will to fight.

name: Malamar
description: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powersof any Pokémon, and it forces others to dowhatever it wants.

name: Binacle
description: Two Binacle live together on one rock.When they fight, one of them will moveto a different rock.

name: Barbaracle
description: When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven.They fight with the power of seven Binacle.

name: Skrelp
description: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they sprayliquid poison on prey that approachesunawares and then finish it off.

name: Dragalge
description: Their poison is strong enough to eat throughthe hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminatelyat anything that enters their territory.

name: Clauncher
description: They knock down flying prey by firingcompressed water from their massiveclaws like shooting a pistol.

name: Clawitzer
description: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs ofwater powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.

name: Helioptile
description: They make their home in deserts. They cangenerate their energy from basking in the sun,so eating food is not a requirement.

name: Heliolisk
description: They flare their frills and generate energy.A single Heliolisk can generate sufficientelectricity to power a skyscraper.

name: Tyrunt
description: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil.If something happens that it doesnt like,it throws a tantrum and runs wild.

name: Tyrantrum
description: Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shredthick metal plates as if they were paper, it wasinvincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.

name: Amaura
description: This ancient Pokémon was restoredfrom part of its body that had beenfrozen in ice for over 100 million years.

name: Aurorus
description: The diamond-shaped crystals on its bodyexpel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit,surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.

name: Sylveon
description: It sends a soothing aura from itsribbonlike feelers to calm fights.

name: Hawlucha
description: Although its body is small, its proficientfighting skills enable it to keep up withbig bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.

name: Dedenne
description: Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending andreceiving electrical waves, it can communicatewith others over vast distances.

name: Carbink
description: Born from the temperatures and pressuresdeep underground, it fires beams from thestone in its head.

name: Goomy
description: The weakest Dragon-type Pokémon,it lives in damp, shady places, so itsbody doesnt dry out.

name: Sliggoo
description: It drives away opponents by excreting asticky liquid that can dissolve anything.Its eyes devolved, so it cant see anything.

name: Goodra
description: This very friendly Dragon-type Pokémonwill hug its beloved Trainer, leavingthat Trainer covered in sticky slime.

name: Klefki
description: These key collectors threaten any attackersby fiercely jingling their keys at them.

name: Phantump
description: These Pokémon are created whenspirits possess rotten tree stumps.They prefer to live in abandoned forests.

name: Trevenant
description: It can control trees at will. It will trap peoplewho harm the forest, so they can never leave.

name: Pumpkaboo
description: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirittrapped in this world. As the sun sets,it becomes restless and active.

name: Gourgeist
description: Singing in eerie voices, they wandertown streets on the night of the new moon.Anyone who hears their song is cursed.

name: Bergmite
description: It blocks opponents attacks with theice that shields its body. It uses cold airto repair any cracks with new ice.

name: Avalugg
description: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel.Its cumbersome frame crushes anything thatstands in its way.

name: Noibat
description: They live in pitch-black caves. Their enormous earscan emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.

name: Noivern
description: They fly around on moonless nightsand attack careless prey. Nothing canbeat them in a battle in the dark.

name: Xerneas
description: Legends say it can share eternal life.It slept for a thousand years in the formof a tree before its revival.

name: Yveltal
description: When this legendary Pokémons wings andtail feathers spread wide and glow red,it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

name: Zygarde
description: This is Zygardes form when it has gathered 50% of its cells. It wipes out all those who oppose it, showing not a shred of mercy.

name: Diancie
description: A sudden transformation of Carbink,its pink, glimmering body is said to bethe loveliest sight in the whole world.

name: Hoopa
description: In its true form, it possesses a huge amount of power. Legends of its avarice tell how it once carried off an entire castle to gain the treasure hidden within.

name: Volcanion
description: It lets out billows of steam and disappears intothe dense fog. Its said to live in mountainswhere humans do not tread.

name: Rowlet
description: This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis tostore up energy during the day, while becomingactive at night.

name: Dartrix
description: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free timepreening its wings. Its preoccupation with anydirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.

name: Decidueye
description: It fires arrow quills from its wings with suchprecision, they can pierce a pebble at distancesover a hundred yards.

name: Litten
description: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside itsstomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fieryattacks, which change based on how it coughs.

name: Torracat
description: At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell ringsbrightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.

name: Incineroar
description: This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition.If its not in the mood to listen, it will ignore itsTrainers orders with complete nonchalance.

name: Popplio
description: This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose,blowing balloons to smash into its foes.Its famous for being a hard worker.

name: Brionne
description: A skillful dancer, it creates a sequence of waterballoons as it dances, and briskly bombardsits enemies.

name: Primarina
description: It controls its water balloons with song. Themelody is learned from others of its kind and ispassed down from one generation to the next.

name: Pikipek
description: It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second todrill holes in trees. It uses the holes for foodstorage and for nesting.

name: Trumbeak
description: It eats berries and stores their seeds in itsbeak. When it encounters enemies or prey,it fires off all the seeds in a burst.

name: Toucannon
description: When it battles, its beak heats up. Thetemperature can easily exceed 212 degreesFahrenheit, causing severe burns when it hits.

name: Yungoos
description: With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything.It did not originally live in Alola but wasimported from another region.

name: Gumshoos
description: When it finds a trace of its prey, it patientlystakes out the location...but its always snoozingby nightfall.

name: Grubbin
description: Its strong jaw enables it to scrape trees andslurp out the sap. It normally lives underground.

name: Charjabug
description: Its body is capable of storing electricity. Oncamping trips, people are grateful to haveone around.

name: Vikavolt
description: It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening.It concentrates electrical energy within its largejaws and uses it to zap its enemies.

name: Crabrawler
description: While guarding its weak points with its pincers,it looks for an opening and unleashes punches.When it loses, it foams at the mouth and faints.

name: Crabominable
description: It aimed for the top but got lost and ended upon a snowy mountain. Being forced to endurethe cold, this Pokémon evolved and grew fur.

name: Oricorio
description: It beats its wings together to create fire.As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance,it bathes opponents in intense flames.

name: Cutiefly
description: It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers.Because its able to sense auras, it can identifywhich flowers are about to bloom.

name: Ribombee
description: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes manydifferent varieties, some used as food andothers used in battle.

name: Rockruff
description: Its considered to be a good Pokémon forbeginners because of its friendliness, but itsdisposition grows rougher as it grows up.

name: Lycanroc
description: Its quick movements confuse its enemies.Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also usesthe sharp rocks in its mane as weapons.

name: Wishiwashi
description: When its in trouble, its eyes moisten and beginto shine. The shining light attracts its comrades,and they stand together against their enemies.

name: Mareanie
description: It plunges the poison spike on its head into itsprey. When the prey has weakened, Mareaniedeals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.

name: Toxapex
description: Toxapex crawls along the ocean floor on its12 legs. It leaves a trail of Corsola bitsscattered in its wake.

name: Mudbray
description: The mud stuck to Mudbrays hooves enhancesits grip and its powerful running gait.

name: Mudsdale
description: It spits a mud that provides resistance to bothwind and rain, so the walls of old houses wereoften coated with it.

name: Dewpider
description: It crawls onto the land in search of food.Its water bubble allows it to breathe andprotects its soft head.

name: Araquanid
description: It delivers headbutts with the water bubbleon its head. Small Pokémon get sucked intothe bubble, where they drown.

name: Fomantis
description: During the day, it sleeps and soaks up light.When night falls, it walks around lookingfor a safer place to sleep.

name: Lurantis
description: It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantissvivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy thiswork and treat it as their hobby.

name: Morelull
description: It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyoneseeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.

name: Shiinotic
description: Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous toenter at night. People confused by its strangelights can never find their way home again.

name: Salandit
description: It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonousgas. When its enemies become disoriented frominhaling the gas, it attacks them.

name: Salazzle
description: For some reason, only females have been found.It creates a reverse harem of male Salandit thatit lives with.

name: Stufful
description: Despite its adorable appearance, when it getsangry and flails about, its arms and legs couldknock a pro wrestler sprawling.

name: Bewear
description: This immensely dangerous Pokémonpossesses overwhelming physical strength.Its habitat is generally off-limits.

name: Bounsweet
description: A delectable aroma pours from its body.They are often swallowed whole by Toucannonlured by that wafting deliciousness.

name: Steenee
description: The sepals on its head developed to protect itsbody. These are quite hard, so even if peckedby bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.

name: Tsareena
description: Its long, striking legs arent just for show but tobe used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows offby kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.

name: Comfey
description: It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine.This revitalizes the flowers, and they give offan aromatic scent.

name: Oranguru
description: Known for its extreme intelligence, this Pokémonwill look down on inexperienced Trainers, so itsbest suited to veteran Trainers.

name: Passimian
description: They form groups of roughly 20 individuals.Their mutual bond is remarkable—they will neverlet down a comrade.

name: Wimpod
description: This Pokémon is a coward. As it desperatelydashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves asparkling clean path in its wake.

name: Golisopod
description: With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws,it cleaves seawater—or even air—right in two.

name: Sandygast
description: Born from a sand mound playfully built by achild, this Pokémon embodies the grudges ofthe departed.

name: Palossand
description: Possessed people controlled by this Pokémontransformed its sand mound into a castle. As itevolved, its power to curse grew ever stronger.

name: Pyukumuku
description: It lives in shallow seas, such as areas near abeach. It can eject its internal organs, which ituses to engulf its prey or battle enemies.

name: Type Null
description: The heavy control mask it wears suppresses itsintrinsic capabilities. This Pokémon has somehidden special power.

name: Silvally
description: Its trust in its partner is what awakens it.This Pokémon is capable of changing its type,a flexibility that is well displayed in battle.

name: Minior
description: Originally making its home in the ozone layer,it hurtles to the ground when the shell enclosingits body grows too heavy.

name: Komala
description: It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All itsmovements are apparently no more than theresults of it tossing and turning in its dreams.

name: Turtonator
description: The shell on its back is chemically unstableand explodes violently if struck. The hole in itsstomach is its weak point.

name: Togedemaru
description: The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest.When this Pokémon becomes agitated, its furstands on end and stabs into its attackers.

name: Mimikyu
description: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholarwho saw what was under its rag wasoverwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.

name: Bruxish
description: When it unleashes its psychic power from theprotuberance on its head, the grating soundof grinding teeth echoes through the area.

name: Drampa
description: It has a compassionate personality, but if it isangered, it completely destroys its surroundingswith its intense breath.

name: Dhelmise
description: Swinging its massive anchor, it can KO Wailordin a single blow. What appears to be greenseaweed is actually its body.

name: Jangmo-o
description: It expresses its feelings by smackingits scales. Metallic sounds echo throughthe tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.

name: Hakamo-o
description: It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout.Its scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.

name: Kommo-o
description: When it spots enemies, it threatens them byjingling the scales on its tail. Weak opponentswill crack and flee in panic.

name: Tapu Koko
description: This guardian deity of Melemele is brimming withcuriosity. It summons thunderclouds and storestheir lightning inside its body.

name: Tapu Lele
description: This guardian deity of Akala is guilelessly cruel.The fragrant aroma of flowers is the source ofits energy.

name: Tapu Bulu
description: It pulls large trees up by the roots and swingsthem around. It causes vegetation to grow,and then it absorbs energy from the growth.

name: Tapu Fini
description: The dense fog it creates brings the downfalland destruction of its confused enemies.Ocean currents are the source of its energy.

name: Cosmog
description: Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowly grows asit collects dust from the atmosphere.

name: Cosmoem
description: Motionless as if dead, its body is faintly warm tothe touch. In the distant past, it was called thecocoon of the stars.

name: Solgaleo
description: It is said to live in another world. The intenselight it radiates from the surface of its body canmake the darkest of nights light up like midday.

name: Lunala
description: It is said to be a female evolution of Cosmog.When its third eye activates, away it flies toanother world.

name: Nihilego
description: One of several mysterious Ultra Beasts. Peopleon the street report observing those infestedby it suddenly becoming violent.

name: Buzzwole
description: This Ultra Beast appeared from another world.It shows off its body, but whether that displayis a boast or a threat remains unclear.

name: Pheromosa
description: One of the dangerous Ultra Beasts, it has beenspotted running across the land atterrific speeds.

name: Xurkitree
description: One of the mysterious life-forms known as UltraBeasts. Astonishing electric shocks emanatefrom its entire body, according to witnesses.

name: Celesteela
description: It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. Witnessesobserved it flying across the sky at high speed.

name: Kartana
description: This Ultra Beast came from the Ultra Wormhole.It seems not to attack enemies on its own, butits sharp body is a dangerous weapon in itself.

name: Guzzlord
description: It has gobbled mountains and swallowed wholebuildings, according to reports. Its one of theUltra Beasts.

name: Necrozma
description: Reminiscent of the Ultra Beasts, this life-form,apparently asleep underground, is thought tohave come from another world in ancient times.

name: Magearna
description: This artificial Pokémon, constructed more than500 years ago, can understand human speechbut cannot itself speak.

name: Marshadow
description: It slips into the shadows of others and mimicstheir powers and movements. As it improves, itbecomes stronger than those its imitating.

name: Poipole
description: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to bechosen as a first partner in its own world.

name: Naganadel
description: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquidinside its body. It is one of the organisms knownas UBs.

name: Stakataka
description: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each oneappears to be made up of many life-formsstacked one on top of each other.

name: Blacephalon
description: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning,it triggers the explosion of its own head.Its apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

name: Zeraora
description: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, theyll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.

name: Meltan
description: It melts particles of iron and other metals foundin the subsoil, so it can absorb them into itsbody of molten steel.

name: Melmetal
description: Revered long ago for its capacity to create ironfrom nothing, for some reason it has come backto life after 3,000 years.
